  <thing id="cuUWWater1" name="Command Water" description="As a standard action, you can enslave creatures with the water subtype within 30 feet. Creatures receive a Will save to negate the effect. The DC for this Will save is equal to 10 + 1/2 your unholy warrior level + your Charisma modifier. Creatures that fail their saves fall under your control, obeying your commands to the best of their ability, like undead as if under the effects of the control undead spell. Intelligent creatures receive a new saving throw each day to resist your command. You can control any number of creatures of the water subtype, so long as their total Hit Dice do not exceed your unholy warrior level. If a water creature is under the control of another creature, you must make an opposed Charisma check whenever your orders conflict. \n\nThe unholy warrior can use this ability a number of times per day equal to 1 + Charisma modifier at 1st level . The unholy warrior gains an additional use of this ability every five levels thereafter (one at 5th, two at 10th, etc.)" compset="ClSpecial" summary="Command water subtype creatures.">
